OL,7,FMembers of the Committee are said to
OL,8,Fhave heard compelling arguments about
OL,9,Fthe risks of injuries and fatalities
OL,10,Fon the track and concerns over the
OL,11,Fwelfare of the dogs from breeding and
OL,12,Fkennelling to retirement. It says it
OL,13,Falso heard of there being a lack of
OL,14,Ftransparency and gaps in data on
OL,15,Finjury rates and lifetime welfare.
